-- Arista Networks files for IPO of up to $200 mln
-- By Aman Shah in Bangalore
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 06:51AM EDT
-- None



March 31 (Reuters) - Arista Networks, a maker of network switches, filed with U.S. regulators to raise up to $200 million in an initial public offering.

The Santa Clara-based company, whose competitors include Cisco Systems Inc <CSCO.O>, listed Morgan Stanley and Citigroup as lead underwriters to the offering in its IPO filing on Monday. [ID:http://r.reuters.com/jaw97v ] The filing did not reveal how many shares the company planned to sell or their expected price.